						<summary>

						<p>This inscription which is badly damaged belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva (Vikramāditya VI)</hi> and seems to register a gift of land made to the god Traipurushadēva of the <hi rend="italic">śāle</hi> at the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tuṁbigi,</hi> by Mahāpradhāna, Hērisandhivigrahi, Manevergaḍe, [Daṇḍa]nāyaka <hi rend="bold">Ni[ṁ*]baṇa.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama year 11, Kshaya, Vaiśākha, puṇṇame, Sunday.</hi> The tithi fell not on Sunday but on Friday, <hi rend="bold">May 1, A.D. 1086.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
